I"Â<p>Iâ€™m using <a href="https://www.telerik.com/help/wpf/radscheduleview-overview.html">Telerikâ€™s RadScheduleView</a> in a WPF project. Double-clicking the grid to create an appointment suddenly stopped working.</p>

<p><em>Turns out</em> I had changed my custom appointment subclassâ€™s default constructor from <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">public</code> to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">protected</code>. The schedule view needs a public default constructor or it will just silently not create new appointments:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>public class MyCustomAppointment
{
    // this is required to double-click to create
    public MyCustomAppointment()
    {
        // ...
    }

    // non-default constructor can still be called in code
    public MyCustomAppointment(...)
    {
        // ...
    }
}
</code></pre></div></div>
